{
  "texts": [
    "In the context of a pre-trained LLM, zero-shot learning leverages the knowledge and understanding embedded in the model from its training on a vast amount of natural language.",
    "When applied to zero-shot learning, the LLM can make informed predictions to identify malicious network traffic by understanding the provided instructions and applying its broad contextual knowledge to classify the traffic as either malicious or benign, even though it hasn't been specifically trained on labelled examples of network attacks.Fine-tuning.",
    "Fine-tuning LLMs for specific tasks is a crucial step to enhance their performance and adapt them to domain-specific requirements.",
    "In our investigation, we focus on two state-of-the-art fine-tuning methods: Odds Ratio Preference Optimisation (ORPO) [19] and Kahneman-Tversky Optimisation (KTO) [20].",
    "These methods have shown significant promise and represent the current state of the art [18]."
  ]
}